1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Where? Here? Maybe nothing!

7
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
What about... here?

8
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Hey, mushrooms! Are you all on vacation or what?

9
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:51,000
I give up! There are no mushrooms anywhere!

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
I don't think there ever were! Bjorn and Bucky!

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Where'd he go? Who can keep up with that bear?

12
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:16,000
What are you doing? Earth to the polar bear!

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
So am I just looking for mushrooms all alone?

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
You had time to find all those mushrooms and have a dance party too?

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Alright Bjorn, tell me how you found them!

16
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Cause I looked everywhere really hard!

17
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
And I found none!

18
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:37,000
I don't really know, Bucky! I'm just totally in tune with nature!

19
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Bjorn and the forest drum to the same beat! And that's how!

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:44,000
But where you come from, there's no forest! Just a lot of snow!

21
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:50,000
There is snow, yeah! But there's forest too! And animals and the ocean! The north is pretty big!

22
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Question! How do you stock up for the winter up north where the world is frozen?

23
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Mushroom-sickles! Just kidding! We dry fish! And there's juicy walrus steaks and yummy fish oil!

24
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Yummy fish oil? So disgusting! Suddenly mushrooms sound a whole lot better!

25
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:16,000
And this bear is going to invent a modern way to fix them! I'll make the forest dance to a brand new drum!

26
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Ugh!

27
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Ha-ha!

28
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,000
With his mighty hammer, the brown bear can change the world!

29
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Hey Bucky, I could use your help! I got all the mushrooms ready to hang up to dry them out for winter!

30
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Mushrooms, mushroom! I'm on a roll here!

31
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Huh?

32
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Check out my amazing invention!

33
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Uh, it's a barrel with warts?

34
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Don't you see? Now every mushroom will be ours!

35
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Thanks to my remarkable machine, the Rushzoomer Mushroomer 500!

36
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:03,000
So, it's not a wart barrel? How is it supposed to gather mushrooms, Bucky?

37
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Prepare to witness the amazing!

38
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:12,000
One humble brown bear is about to show the whole entire world the way a master stalks up for the winter!

39
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Ha-ha! Ha-ha! Ha-ha! Ha-ha! Ha-ha!

40
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Yeah! Bjornie, look! Woo-hoo! Yeah! I love it!

41
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:25,000
I'm a rushzoomin' my tail off! Bucky the Bear is a genius! Ha-ha-ha! Ha-ha-ha!

42
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Oh-oh-oh! Ha-he-ha-ha!

43
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:32,000
Yeah! Rushzoom! Gotcha! Gotcha-toot! Gotcha-toot! Ha-ha!

44
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Ha-ha! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

45
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Well then, do you love it or do you love it? Greatest invention in bear history!

46
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:45,000
But Bucky, there's a lot of stuff, just not the right stuff.

47
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Just look! Try! Dig around, you'll find mushrooms in there!

48
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Well, I found some really nice leaves!

49
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
The wonderful bounty of the forest! Looks great!

50
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Mmm!

51
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Bleh! That tastes truly awful!

52
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,000
What if we mixed it with that yummy fish oil you were talking about?

53
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Wait, that's the worst idea ever.

54
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,000
The polar bear is getting...

55
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,000
A pretty cool idea! Bucky, listen!

56
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:20,000
I already know it. The rushzoomer is nothing but a wart barrel.

57
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:27,000
My big important machine for picking mushrooms is a failure.

58
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Bucky, it was not a failure.

59
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,000
While it may not be the best machine for collecting mushrooms,

60
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
it is super good at cleaning old leaves up.

61
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,000
I'm a genius! Ha-ha!

62
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Just look at the...

63
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,000
D-leafinator 5000!

64
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,000
But I can make it even better!

65
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Maybe...

66
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
What it needs is a motor!

67
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Just a zillion or so horsepower and...

68
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
I could hook you up with some reindeer.

69
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Forget reindeer and horses!

70
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,000
We can use genuine bear power!

71
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Ha-ha!

72
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Ha-ha!

73
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Ha-ha!

74
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,000
Ha-ha-ha!

75
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Ha-ha-ha!

76
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Ha-ha-ha!

77
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Ha-ha-ha!

78
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Ha-ha-ha!

79
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,000
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

80
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

81
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Yeah!

82
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Woo-hoo!

83
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,000
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

84
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Bucky is up!

85
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Bucky and Bjorn are both geniuses!

86
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Best bear buddies, they've got the goods!

87
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,000
With their wonderful wagon cleaning up the woods!

88
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Singing songs and cracking jokes!

89
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,000
We'll see you next time!

90
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Cause that's all, folks!

91
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,000
B-b-b-b-bears!

92
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Uh, did you put brakes on this thing?

